  "prompt": "What's that device on umpire's arm?",
  "response": "The device on an umpire's arm is typically a signal device that helps them communicate with other officials and keep track of game statistics, such as pitch calls in baseball or tennis scores. \n\nIn some sports, such as tennis, umpires use a device known as an \"electronic scorecard\" or \"communication device\" to relay scores and match information. In baseball and some other sports, they might use a wrist-mounted device to assist with tracking pitches and calls.\n\nIf you have a specific sport in mind, let me know, and I can provide more detailed information!",
